<materialsCitation collectingDate="1998-03-29" collectingDateMax="1998-08-31" collectingDateMin="1998-03-29" collectionCode="RMGC" collectorName="The &amp; Dave Marqua &amp; Limpia Canyon &amp; Two &amp; R. M. Gemmill &amp; Klondike Rd. Gemmill &amp; This" county="Jeff Davis Co." elevation="1800" location="Eddy Co." municipality="Davis Mts." pageId="8" pageNumber="746" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Texas">
Until the 1980s, this species was known from only a few specimens. Numerous specimens were collected after 1990 from TX: 
<collectingCounty box="[437,574,1491,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Jeff Davis Co.</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingMunicipality pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Davis Mts.</collectingMunicipality>
by D. G. 
<collectingMethod box="[305,638,1518,1539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Marqua in fermenting sugar traps</collectingMethod>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MacRae, T. C." box="[158,295,1545,1566]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" pagination="137 - 169" refId="ref9403" refString="MacRae, T. C. 2000. Review of the genus Purpuricenus Dejean (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) in North America. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 76 (3): 137 - 169." type="journal article" year="2000">MacRae 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[310,347,1545,1566]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">The</collectorName>
late 
<collectorName box="[390,519,1545,1566]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Dave Marqua</collectorName>
collected all of his specimens near his residence located in 
<collectorName box="[151,303,1600,1621]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Limpia Canyon</collectorName>
at about 
<quantity box="[402,483,1600,1621]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" unit="m" value="1800.0">
<elevation box="[402,483,1600,1621]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" unit="m" value="1800.0">1,800 m</elevation>
</quantity>
elevation. 
<collectorName box="[595,637,1600,1621]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Two</collectorName>
specimens were reared by 
<collectorName box="[402,546,1627,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">R. M. Gemmill</collectorName>
(
<collectionCode box="[558,631,1627,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">RMGC</collectionCode>
) from NM: 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1A26C542FF074973FF07882FD035FEB6:9750228FFF074973FF698B31D54CF97C" box="[249,339,1654,1675]" county="Jeff Davis Co." municipality="Davis Mts." name="Eddy Co." pageId="8" pageNumber="746" stateProvince="Texas">Eddy Co.</location>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1A26C542FF074973FF07882FD035FEB6:9750228FFF074973FECA8B31D629F97C" box="[346,566,1654,1675]" county="Jeff Davis Co." municipality="Davis Mts." name="Lincoln National Forest" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" stateProvince="Texas">Lincoln National Forest</location>
, 
<locationDeviation location="Hwy" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">
<quantity box="[574,621,1654,1675]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.609344" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" unit="mi" value="1.0">1 mi.</quantity>
S Hwy
</locationDeviation>
137 on 
<collectorName box="[303,536,1682,1703]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1A26C542FF074973FF07882FD035FEB6:9750228FFF074973FEBF8BD5D5A8F950" box="[303,439,1682,1703]" county="Jeff Davis Co." municipality="Davis Mts." name="Klondike Rd." pageId="8" pageNumber="746" stateProvince="Texas">
Klondike 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1A26C542FF074973FF07882FD035FEB6:9750228FFF074973FE058BD5D5A8F950" box="[405,439,1682,1703]" county="Jeff Davis Co." municipality="Davis Mts." name="Rd. Gemmill" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" stateProvince="Texas">Rd.</location>
</location>
Gemmill
</collectorName>
(personal communication) collected dead/dying oak (
<taxonomicName box="[552,630,1709,1730]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,630,1709,1730]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) branches on 
<date box="[813,923,194,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" value="1998-03-29">
<collectingDate box="[813,923,194,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" value="1998-03-29">29-III-1998</collectingDate>
</date>
, and adults emerged (indoors) in 
<date box="[783,1007,220,241]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" value="1998-06" valueMax="1998-08-31" valueMin="1998-06-00">
<collectingDate box="[783,1007,220,241]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" value="1998-06" valueMax="1998-08-31" valueMin="1998-06-00">June and August 1998</collectingDate>
</date>
. 
<collectorName box="[1020,1062,220,241]" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">This</collectorName>
location is close to the 
<collectingRegion box="[805,859,247,268]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">Texas</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
/ 
<materialsCitation box="[866,989,247,268]" collectingDate="1998-03-29" collectingDateMax="1998-08-31" collectingDateMin="1998-03-29" collectionCode="RMGC" collectorName="The &amp; Dave Marqua &amp; Limpia Canyon &amp; Two &amp; R. M. Gemmill &amp; Klondike Rd. Gemmill &amp; This" county="Jeff Davis Co." elevation="1800" isTailEnumeration="true" location="Eddy Co." municipality="Davis Mts." pageId="8" pageNumber="746" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="New Mexico">
<collectingRegion box="[866,989,247,268]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="746">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation location="Sacramento Mountains" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="New Mexico">
border, suggesting that this species may occur farther northwest into the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1A26C542FF074973FF07882FD035FEB6:9750228FFF074973FD3D8C6BD799FEB6" box="[685,902,300,321]" name="Sacramento Mountains" pageId="8" pageNumber="746" stateProvince="New Mexico">Sacramento Mountains</location>
